Civil rights activist is more accurate than political activist.
Changed "group" to "organisation". AfriForum is a civil rights organisation.

Ernst Roets is now the Head of Policy and Action at AfriForum. AfriForum is a civil rights organisation, not a white nationalist organisations. They have publicly condemned white nationalism. See link: https://www.afriforum.co.za/en/afriforums-rejection-of-white-nationalism/

This description is not neutral. To say AfriForum is a white nationalist organisation is a FACTUAL MISTAKE. AfriForum is a CIVIL RIGHTS ORGANISATION.Some of the sources are opinion pieces, others contain inaccurate information. Please see examples where AfriForum condemns white nationalist groups: https://www.iol.co.za/dailynews/news/afriforum-condemns-kommando-camps-1242844 / https://m.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/AfriForum-condemns-racist-Dan-Roodt-20141113 /
Previous changes to this page was not neutral and the facts represented are completely inaccurate.
I have added more sources. It seems that whoever is editing this page only adds one sided sources - some of which are opinion pieces and not factual sources which is very bias.

Added "civil rights organisation" in the intro. Moved some of the information to different areas. The introduction included criticism and controversies, which I moved to the correct sections. It's bias to include that in the introduction. It should be under criticism and controversy.
